org.agilewiki.jactor2.core.requests

Interface AsyncResponseProcessor<RESPONSE_TYPE>

  • Type Parameters:
    RESPONSE_TYPE - The type of response.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AsyncNativeRequest<RESPONSE_TYPE>, AsyncRequestImpl<RESPONSE_TYPE>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BoundResponseProcessor, DelayAOp, OneWayResponseProcessor, SAOp, SignalResponseProcessor

    public interface AsyncResponseProcessor<RESPONSE_TYPE>
    An AsyncResponseProcessor is an application callback to handle the response from a request.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void processAsyncResponse(RESPONSE_TYPE _response)
      The processAsyncResponse method accepts the response of a request.

    • Method Detail

      • processAsyncResponse

        void processAsyncResponse(RESPONSE_TYPE _response)
                   throws java.lang.Exception
        The processAsyncResponse method accepts the response of a request.

        This method need not be thread-safe, as it is always invoked from the same light-weight thread (targetReactor) that passed the AsyncRequest and AsyncResponseProcessor objects.

        Parameters:
        _response - The response to a request.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
